@2000 = ~The history of this weapon lost its significance in the great ocean of stories that are told about the High Forest, but the song of the outstanding archer Adaniss Rhyte is still sung by many bards:

Shocked by the power of his bow
Quickly falls the game struck by Adaniss
Many years ago at the time of the Quiet Earth
During the hunt in the legendary High Forest.

The Duke of Everlund always boasted very much
The trophies, which he lined up
But his anger was inflamed by another hunter
Whose prey of a year exceeded his own.

A dark tragedy befell one morning the land
The death of the Duke's most magnificent dog.
Fallen at the foot of a great elm tree
The arrow still stuck in its throat.

With a keen eye, he found the game fore sure.
His hands firm and graceful
Aiming at the fey target
No shot was too difficult for Adaniss Rhyte.

That same evening Adaniss turned to the Duke.
To atone for grave mistake that he had made.
But the anger of the nobleman demanded ten pounds of meat
And they pulled the archer's arm out of its joints.

Unlawfulness for justice demands the Duke
The worst spell cursing his arm.
He sought revenge for price he had paid
And so Rhyte swore the arrow for the dog was not the last.

Worried the city helped forge an ax
Blessed to prove him the honor a famed day.
The scar of Rhytes arrow as a guide for the ax
And they say, it also kills with one hit.

With a keen eye, he found the game fore sure.
His hands firm and graceful
Aiming at the fey target
No shot was too difficult for Adaniss Rhyte.

Again, the Forest called with its precious wild
In search of prey  Adaniss roamed the lands.
The Blood Falcon was the price that he wanted
And on the Lost Peaks was where he would find it.

Once again, the rivalry of the Duke was stirring
Confident of his strength with the bow of Rhyte
His focus on the magnificent bird
The next heir is safe from all harm.

Both climbed the summit and sought for endless days
Their will power was of the strength of stones.
They met by chance at a rocky cliff
Both full of hatred running deep in their bones.

With a keen eye, he found the game fore sure.
His hands firm and graceful
Aiming at the fey target
No shot was too difficult for Adaniss Rhyte.

The Duke drew the bow and pulled the string
But before flew Adaniss' ax so very quick.
His skull split, the Duke stumbled to the rocky edge and fell
Defeated by Rhytes last arrow...

With a keen eye, he found the game fore sure.
His hands firm and graceful
Aiming at the fey target
No shot was too difficult for Adaniss Rhyte.
No shot was too difficult for Adaniss Rhyte.

