@2019 = ~This finely crafted battle staff is one of the treasures left behind by the invaders in Durlag tower. It is deadly in combat, and probably belonged to a spell caster, who equally enjoyed fighting at the front. Apparently the staff has an iron core, and yet its weight is comparable to a normal weapon of this type. Part of the enchantment seems to come from the hide that wraps the handle. The leather is undoubtedly from a creature that was surely battle-tested. The taste and inclination of the tower attackers are well documented, but the fur still could stem from anything ... or anyone.

